x4freetext: High-flux reactor.
Samples were produced from the Isol-system OSTIS at
exp. neutron beam of reactor.The mass contamination
about 10**-5 .
Gamma-ray, conversion and beta-delayed neutron
spectroscopy.
Flight paths 0.6 m - 2.5 m; 30 - 50 cm.
*** For Gamma-ray and Conversion electron Spectroscopy:
For spectra of gamma-rays and conversion
electrons. Placed at 3 cm distance from the source.
Ge(Li) - relative efficiency 25%, resolution 2.1 keV at
1.3 MeV.
Si(Li) - 5 mm thickness, 300 mm2 surface, resolution
1.7 keV at 624 keV.
Ge(Li) or Si(Li) detector could be replaced by
1 mm thick plastic scintillator to define life-time of
excited states from delayed beta-electron or beta-gamma
coincidence. Resolving time 2TAU = 5 nsec.
Second Ge(Li) replacing Si(Li) detector - for
gamma-gamma coincidence, resolving time 15 nsec.
Transitions used for internal calibration of conversion
electrons :
Isotope    E-gamma,keV           Multipolarity
*** For Spectroscopy of Beta-Delayed Neutrons :
Three identical He-3 ionization chambers
for neutron detection; 100 cm3 Ge(Li) diode for
gamma-ray detection.
Energy resolution 12 keV for thermal neutrons, about
20 keV for 1 MeV neutrons. Resolving time 5 microsec.
5 inch diameter liquid scintillator NE213 for
TOF (paths 0.6 m - 2.5 m) measurement of neutron single
and neutron-gamma coincidence spectra in energy range
180 keV - 3 MeV.
Li-glass detector to measure low-energy (5 keV
- 150 keV) spectrum at flight paths 30 -50  cm.
The intensities of beta-branches were determined from
a filiation measurement assuming
- for Rb-95 - the 954 keV gamma-line
of Zr-95 intensity of 0.19+-0.02 from REL-REF of
P.Cavallini+ and taking the neutron emission
probability Pn=(8.6+-0.5)% from REL-REF of C.Ristory+;
- for Rb-97 - intensity of the 743 keV gamma-line of
Nb-97 0.928 from REL-REF of C.M.Lederer+ and Pn value
of Rb-97 25.2% from REL-REF of C.Ristori+ .
